The United Nations denounced the "disdain for international humanitarian law" and its operators, while US President Joe Biden called himself "indignant", after stating that Israel "is not doing enough" to protect those who come to help the " hungry" Palestinian population. The Israeli attack against the seven members of the World Central Kitchen "has the characteristics of a precision air strike, which indicates that the Israeli army intended to hit these vehicles", said Richard Weir of the NGO Human Rights Watch (HRW), according to a press release. Since the beginning of the war, 196 humanitarian workers have been killed, including 175 UN operators, according to Secretary General Antonio Guterres.
